The Gulabi Gang (from Hindi गुलाबी gulabī, "pink") is a group of Indian women activists. The group first appeared in Bundelkhand, Uttar Pradesh, as a response to widespread domestic abuse and other violence against women. It was founded by Data Satbodh Sain and was previously commanded by Sampat Pal Devi. The group consists of women between eighteen and sixty years old. It is reported to have spread and since 2010, it has been active across North India., both on the streets and in local politics.
